<section id="slide-org7ae8509" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h2 id="org7ae8509">0.0: Preliminaries</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org7ae8509">
</div>
</section>
<section id="slide-org2e99adf" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h3 id="org2e99adf">Prerequisites</h3>
<ul>
<li>students should be familiar with 
<ul>
<li>powers and indices</li>
<li>Standard form/scientific notation</li>

</ul></li>

</ul>
</section>
</section>
<section>
<section id="slide-org84e0657" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h2 id="org84e0657">1.0: Dimensions</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org84e0657">
</div>
</section>
<section id="slide-org4074035" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h3 id="org4074035">1.1: Base dimensions</h3>
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">All quantities in mechanics are composed of three base quantities refered to as dimensions.</li>

</ul>
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">length, \(\left[ \rm{L} \right]\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">time, \(\left[ \rm{T} \right]\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">mass, \(\left[ \rm{M} \right]\)</li>

</ul>

<ul style="text-align:left">
<li data-fragment-index="3" class="fragment roll-in">when discussing electricity and magnetism we also include</li>

</ul>

<ul style="text-align:left">
<li data-fragment-index="4" class="fragment roll-in">charge, \(\left[ \rm{Q} \right]\)</li>

</ul>

</section>
<section id="slide-orgbbab6fe" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h3 id="orgbbab6fe">1.2: Dimensional combinations</h3>
<p class="fragment (roll-in)" style="text-align:left">
Combinations of these base quantities make up other quantities
</p>
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li class="fragment roll-in">speed, \(\left[ \rm{L} \right] \left[ \rm{T} \right]^{-1}\)</li>
<li class="fragment roll-in">acceleration, \(\left[ \rm{L} \right] \left[ \rm{T} \right]^{-2}\)</li>
<li class="fragment roll-in">momentum, \(\left[ \rm{M} \right] \left[ \rm{L} \right] \left[ \rm{T} \right]^{-2}\)</li>
<li class="fragment roll-in">kinetic energy, \(\left[ \rm{M} \right] \left[ \rm{L} \right]^2 \left[ \rm{T} \right]^{-2}\)</li>

</ul>
</section>
<section id="slide-orgdf0411c" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h3 id="orgdf0411c">1.3.1 Exercises \(-\) 1</h3>
<p style="text-align:left">
What are the quantites described by the following dimensional combinations?
</p>
<div class="column" style="float:left; width: 50%">
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">\(\left[ \rm{L} \right] \left[ \rm{T} \right]^{-2}\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">\(\left[ \rm{M} \right] \left[ \rm{L} \right]^{-3}\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">\(\left[ \rm{L} \right]^{2}\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">\(\left[ \rm{M} \right] \left[ \rm{L} \right]^{2} \left[ \rm{T} \right]^{-2}\)</li>

</ul>
</div>

<div class="column" style="float:right; width: 50%">
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">speed or velocity</li>
<li data-fragment-index="3" class="fragment roll-in">density</li>
<li data-fragment-index="4" class="fragment roll-in">area</li>
<li data-fragment-index="5" class="fragment roll-in">energy</li>

</ul>
</div>
</section>
<section id="slide-org00038c0" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h3 id="org00038c0">1.3.2 Exercises \(-\) 2</h3>
<p style="text-align:left">
What are the dimensional combinations for the following quantities?
</p>
<div class="column" style="float:left; width: 50%">
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">force</li>
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">momentum</li>
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">cycles per second</li>
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">electric current</li>

</ul>
</div>

<div class="column" style="float:right; width: 50%">
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li class="fragment roll-in">\(\left[ \rm{M} \right] \left[ \rm{L} \right] \left[ \rm{T} \right]^{-2}\)</li>
<li class="fragment roll-in">\(\left[ \rm{M} \right] \left[ \rm{L} \right] \left[ \rm{T} \right]^{-1}\)</li>
<li class="fragment roll-in">\(\left[ \rm{T} \right]^{-1}\)</li>
<li class="fragment roll-in">\(\left[ \rm{Q} \right]\left[ \rm{T} \right]^{-1}\)</li>

</ul>
</div>
</section>
</section>
<section>
<section id="slide-org8baf41e" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h2 id="org8baf41e">2.0: Units</h2>
<p class="fragment (roll-in) ;frag_idx (1)" style="text-align:left">
Units are essentially dimensions that are given a magnitude (size)
</p>
</section>
<section id="slide-org9d9aa8e" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h3 id="org9d9aa8e">2.1: Length</h3>
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">metre \(\left(\rm{m}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">foot \(\left(\rm{ft}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">mile \(\left(\rm{mi}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">furlong \(\left(\rm{fur}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">fathom \(\left(\rm{ftm}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">lightyear \(\left(\rm{ly}\right)\)</li>

</ul>
</section>
<section id="slide-org671d115" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h3 id="org671d115">2.1.1: Time</h3>
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">second \(\left(\rm{s}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">day \(\left(\rm{d}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">year \(\left(\rm{yr}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">svedberg \(\left(\rm{S}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">jiffy</li>
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">lustrum</li>
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">millenium \(\left(\rm{M}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">megannum</li>
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">aeon \(\left(\rm{AE}\right)\)</li>

</ul>
</section>
<section id="slide-org6296226" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h3 id="org6296226">2.1.2: Mass</h3>
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">kilogram \(\left(\rm{kg}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">tonne \(\left(\rm{t}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">slug \(\left(\rm{sl}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">pound \(\left(\rm{lb}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">atomic mass unit \(\left(\rm{u}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">electronvolt \(\left(\rm{eV}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">solar mass \(\left(\rm{M_{\odot}}\right)\)</li>

</ul>
</section>
<section id="slide-org3122421" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h3 id="org3122421">2.2 SI base units</h3>
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">International system of units (Système international d'unités)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">base system known as metre-kilogram-second (MKS)</li>

</ul>
<ul>
<li data-fragment-index="3" class="fragment roll-in">length, metre \(\left(\rm{m}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="3" class="fragment roll-in">time, second \(\left(\rm{s}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="3" class="fragment roll-in">mass, kilogram \(\left(\rm{kg}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="4" class="fragment roll-in">charge, coulomb \(\left(\rm{C}\right)\)</li>

</ul>
</section>
<section id="slide-orga978e55" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h3 id="orga978e55">2.3 SI derived units</h3>
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">SI base units are combined to yield so called derived units</li>

</ul>
<ul>
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">speed, metres per second, \(\left(\rm{m\, s^{-1}}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">force, newtons, \(\left(\rm{N} \equiv \rm{kg\, m\, s^{-2}}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">energy, joules, \(\left(\rm{J} \equiv \rm{N\,m} \equiv \rm{kg\, m^{2}\, s^{-2}}\right)\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="3" class="fragment roll-in">electric current, ampere, \(\left(\rm{A} \equiv \rm{C\, s^{-1}}\right)\)</li>

</ul>
</section>
<section id="slide-orga55ef2a" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h3 id="orga55ef2a">2.4 Exercises \(-\) 3</h3>
<p style="text-align:left">
What is the correct combination of SI base units that describe the following quantities?
</p>
<div class="column" style="float:left; width: 50%">
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">mass per unit length</li>
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">charge per unit area</li>
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">power</li>
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">pressure</li>

</ul>
</div>

<div class="column" style="float:right; width: 50%">
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li data-fragment-index="3" class="fragment roll-in">\(\rm{kg \, m^{-1}}\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="4" class="fragment roll-in">\(\rm{C \, m^{-2}}\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="5" class="fragment roll-in">\(\rm{W} \equiv \rm{J \, s^{-1}} \equiv \rm{N \, m \ s^{-1}} \equiv \rm{kg \, m^{2} \, s^{-3}}\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="6" class="fragment roll-in">\(\rm{Pa} \equiv \rm{N \, m^{-2}} \equiv \rm{kg \, m^{-1} \, s^{-2}}\)</li>

</ul>
</div>
</section>
<section id="slide-org3fa5fd4" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h3 id="org3fa5fd4">2.5 Exercises \(-\) 4</h3>
<p style="text-align:left">
What quantities are described by the following combination of SI base units?
</p>
<div class="column" style="float:left; width: 50%">
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">\(\rm{kg\, m\, s^{-2}}\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">\(\rm{kg\, m\, s^{-1}}\)</li>
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">\(\rm{s^{-1}}\)</li>

</ul>
</div>

<div class="column" style="float:right; width: 50%">
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li data-fragment-index="3" class="fragment roll-in">force</li>
<li data-fragment-index="4" class="fragment roll-in">momentum</li>
<li data-fragment-index="5" class="fragment roll-in">cycles per second, frequency</li>

</ul>
</div>
</section>
</section>
<section>
<section id="slide-orge2f56f2" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h2 id="orge2f56f2">3 SI prefixes</h2>
<p class="fragment (roll-in) ;frag_idx (1)" style="text-align:left">
large and small amounts of physical values may be quantified with prefixes 
</p>
</section>
<section id="slide-org321f718" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h3 id="org321f718">3.1 Some SI prefixes</h3>
<table border="2" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="6" rules="groups" frame="hsides" class="fragment (roll-in) ;frag_idx (1)" style="text-align:left">


<colgroup>
<col  class="org-left" />

<col  class="org-left" />

<col  class="org-left" />
</colgroup>
<thead>
<tr>
<th scope="col" class="org-left">designation</th>
<th scope="col" class="org-left">symbol</th>
<th scope="col" class="org-left">value</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="org-left">tera</td>
<td class="org-left">T</td>
<td class="org-left">\(10^{12}\)</td>
