<section id="slide-org0897e1e" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h3 id="org0897e1e">3.3.0 Exercises \(-\) 5.0</h3>
<p style="text-align:left">
Describe the following quantities by 
</p>
<ul>
<li data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">determining the units of the answer</li>
<li data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">giving your answer with 
<ul>
<li>SI units specified in the question quantified by using scientific notation</li>
<li>SI prefixed derived units</li>

</ul></li>

</ul>
</section>
<section id="slide-org232be15" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h3 id="org232be15">3.3.1 Exercises \(-\) 5.1</h3>
<dl style="text-align:left">
<dt data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">Question</dt><dd data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">The speed of a particle travels 5 centimetres in 10 nanoseconds</dd>
<dt data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">Answer</dt><dd data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">\(5\times 10^{6} {\rm m \, s^{-1}} = 5 \, {\rm Mm \, s^{-1}}\)</dd>

</dl>
</section>
<section id="slide-org1f13472" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h3 id="org1f13472">3.3.2 Exercises \(-\) 5.2</h3>
<dl style="text-align:left">
<dt data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">Question</dt><dd data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">The work done on a body when a force of 1 kilonewton is applied to the body for a distance of 7 nanometres</dd>
<dt data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">Answer</dt><dd data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">\(7 \times 10^{-6} {\rm N \, m} = 7 \,{\rm\unicode{181}J}\)</dd>

</dl>
</section>
<section id="slide-org11a70a7" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h3 id="org11a70a7">3.3.3 Exercises \(-\) 5.3</h3>
<dl style="text-align:left">
<dt data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">Question</dt><dd data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">The force exerted on a body of mass 1 tonne that is accelerated by 6 micrometers per millisecond per millisecond.</dd>
<dt data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">Answer</dt><dd data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">\(6 \times 10^{3} {\rm kg \, m \, s^{-2}} = 6 \,{\rm
               kN}\)</dd>

</dl>
</section>
<section id="slide-orga5c5b5b" data-background="../../images/SLIDE-WIDE_BG-blue_SmlLogo-top-right.png" data-background-size="cover" data-background-opacity="1">
<h3 id="orga5c5b5b">3.3.4 Exercises \(-\) 5.4</h3>
<dl style="text-align:left">
<dt data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">Question</dt><dd data-fragment-index="1" class="fragment roll-in">The the pressure exerted by a cylindrical body of mass
4.33 kilotonne that has a circular cross section of
diameter 30 centimetres that is under under the
influence of gravity in contact with a
flat surface.</dd>
<dt data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">Answer</dt><dd data-fragment-index="2" class="fragment roll-in">\(6.00 \times 10^{8} {\rm kg \, m^{-1} \, s^{-2}} = 600
               \,{\rm MPa} = 0.600 \,{\rm GPa}\)</dd>

</dl>
</section>
</section>
